  "title": "IT Administrator (Coding) @ Changi (1 Year Renewable Contract)",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Details:</strong></u></p><ul><li>1 Year Contract (Renewable)</li><li>Location: 980 Upper Changi Rd N, Singapore 507708</li><li>Working hours: 8am to 4.30pm</li><li>Hourly Rated: $30 - $35/Hour</li></ul><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>A positive, solution-oriented individual, and a strong team player.</li><li>Provide administrative support to the Vice Principal Office, Teachers, and Tertiary Level courses.</li><li><u><strong>Provide IT assistance in setting up the Computer Lab.</strong></u></li><li><u><strong>Has programming and coding skills to assist in office automation tasks (eg, using UiPath, Microsoft Visual Studio).</strong></u></li><li>Assist in maintaining student records and generating data reports.</li><li>Provide logistical support for school operations and events.</li></ul><p><br /><em>\"This is in partnership with the Employment and Employability Institute Pte Ltd (“e2i”).</em></p><p><em>e2i is the empowering network for workers and employers seeking employment and employability solutions. e2i serves as a bridge between workers and employers, connecting with workers to offer job security through job-matching, career guidance and skills upgrading services, and partnering employers to address their manpower needs through recruitment, training, and job redesign solutions. e2i is a tripartite initiative of the National Trades Union Congress set up to support nation-wide manpower and skills upgrading initiatives. By applying for this role, you consent to RMA Groups’s PDPA and </em><u><em>e2i’s PDPA</em></u><em>.\"</em></p>",
